[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability has been detected in the Apache [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTika CSV/Text parser. The fuzzer discovered that the `TextAndCSVParser` class [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to make an outbound HTTPS connection to `jazzer.com:[0m[1;36m443[0m[39m` when processing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcertain input data. This represents a security issue where untrusted input data can[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrigger network requests to arbitrary destinations, potentially leading to data [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexfiltration or exposure of internal services.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability, classified as a medium [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseverity security issue. SSRF vulnerabilities occur when an application accepts [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted input and uses it to make network requests without proper validation, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowing attackers to make the server initiate connections to arbitrary [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdestinations.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Details[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack trace reveals that the vulnerability is triggered during the parsing of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCSV/Text content. The execution flow shows:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The fuzzer entry point is `[0m[1;35mTextAndCSVParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls `[0m[1;35mparseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The parsing is delegated to [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.csv.TextAndCSVParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. During parsing, the method `[0m[1;35mprocessCell[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is invoked to handle individual cell [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontent[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Subsequently, `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called, which attempts to establish an HTTPS [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnection[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. The connection attempt proceeds through Java's standard networking stack [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`HttpURLConnection`, `SSLSocketImpl`, `[0m[1;35mSocket.connect[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. The SSRF sanitizer detects and reports the attempted connection to [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`jazzer.com:[0m[1;36m443[0m[39m`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Automatic URL Processing**: The `TextAndCSVParser` appears to automatically [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetect and process URLs found within CSV cell content, triggering actual network [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnections rather than just extracting or validating the URL format.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Cell Content as Attack Vector**: The vulnerability is exploited at the cell [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing level, indicating that any URL-like content within CSV cells could [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially trigger outbound requests.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Method Chain**: The critical path involves `[0m[1;35mprocessCell[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere the latter method appears to be responsible for initiating the actual network[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnection.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **No Input Validation**: The parser appears to lack proper validation or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitization of URLs before attempting to connect to them, treating cell content as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrusted data.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Investigation[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a comprehensive understanding of this vulnerability, the following [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents should be examined:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`org.apache.tika.parser.csv.TextAndCSVParser` class**:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method implementation to understand why and how it [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitiates connections[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mprocessCell[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to determine how it identifies and routes URL [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontent[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mparse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to understand the overall parsing logic and configuration[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moptions[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any configuration flags or options that control URL processing behavior[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **URL Detection Logic**: [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How the parser identifies content as URLs within cells[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether there are any patterns or heuristics used for URL detection[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If there are configuration options to disable automatic URL processing[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Related Text Parsers**:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether similar URL processing occurs in other text-based parsers in Apache [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTika[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If there are shared utility methods or base classes that implement URL [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Security Controls**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether there are any existing URL allowlist/blocklist mechanisms[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If there are configuration options to restrict network access during parsing[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any documented security considerations for parsing untrusted CSV/text content[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Use Case Justification**:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The intended purpose of fetching URLs during CSV parsing[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether this is a feature designed for specific use cases or an unintended [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Documentation regarding the expected behavior of the parser with URL content[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy for SSRF Vulnerability in TextAndCSVParser[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe SSRF vulnerability exists in the `[0m[1;35mTextAndCSVParser.processURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, which:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Accepts untrusted URLs from CSV cell content containing Excel-style HYPERLINK [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformulas[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Opens a `URLConnection` and fetches content WITHOUT any validation or security [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m275[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m278[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Makes the network request BEFORE consulting the [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.shouldParseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Has no configuration option to disable this behavior[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Bypasses all existing Tika security controls [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDocumentSelector, EmptyParser [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability is triggered when:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. A CSV file contains a cell with `=[0m[1;35mHYPERLINK[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"url"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"display_text"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` formula[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The `HYPERLINK_PATTERN` regex matches [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m251[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mprocessCell[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m261[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` immediately fetches the URL without validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m275[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m278[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix Strategy[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix requires a **defense-in-depth approach** with multiple layers:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Layer [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add Configuration Control [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPrimary Fix[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File:** [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-text-[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodule/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/csv/TextAndCSVConfig.java`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a security configuration flag following the PDFParserConfig pattern:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add a boolean field `fetchHyperlinkContent` that defaults to `false` for [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Add getter and setter methods with `@Field` annotation for XML configuration[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Include comprehensive Javadoc documentation warning about SSRF risks [0m[1;39m([0m[39msimilar to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDFParserConfig.extractInlineImages[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Document that the default is `false` and users should [0m[32m"set to true only with the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mgreatest caution"[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Layer [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Respect [0m[1;35mshouldParseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Check [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSecondary Defense[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File:** [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-text-[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodule/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/csv/TextAndCSVParser.java`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify `[0m[1;35mprocessCell[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m266[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Before calling `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m261[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, check BOTH:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new configuration flag `[0m[1;35mtextAndCSVConfig.isFetchHyperlinkContent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The embedded document extractor's `[0m[1;35mshouldParseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmetadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Only invoke `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if BOTH conditions are true:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Create metadata for the hyperlink[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Metadata hyperlinkMetadata = new [0m[1;35mMetadata[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;35mhyperlinkMetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY, name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Check configuration AND shouldParseEmbedded BEFORE fetching[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtextAndCSVConfig.isFetchHyperlinkContent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mex.shouldParseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhyperlinkMetadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39murl, name, xhtml, metadata, context[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. This ensures:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Feature is opt-in [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaults to OFF[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Respects DocumentSelector and EmptyParser patterns[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Network request only happens if explicitly allowed[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Layer [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Add URL Validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDefense in Depth[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File:** [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-text-[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodule/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/csv/TextAndCSVParser.java`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd URL scheme validation in `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m268[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m285[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Before creating the URL object [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m275[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, validate the URL scheme[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Only allow safe schemes like [0m[32m"http"[0m[39m and [0m[32m"https"[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Reject dangerous schemes like [0m[32m"file"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"ftp"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"jar"[0m[39m, etc.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Add this check immediately after line [0m[1;36m274[0m[39m:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate URL scheme to prevent SSRF[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35murlString.matches[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"^https?://.*"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Blocked attempt to fetch non-HTTP[0m[32m([0m[32mS[0m[32m)[0m[32m URL from HYPERLINK: "[0m[39m + [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39murlString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mparentMetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCoreProperties.EMBEDDED_EXCEPTION, [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[32m"URL scheme not allowed: "[0m[39m + urlString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m:** Modify `TextAndCSVConfig.java`[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add private field: `private boolean fetchHyperlinkContent = false;`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add getter: `public boolean [0m[1;35misFetchHyperlinkContent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add setter with `@Field` annotation and comprehensive Javadoc documenting SSRF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrisks[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m:** Modify `TextAndCSVParser.java` - [0m[1;35mprocessCell[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m260[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter creating the anchor tag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, get the EmbeddedDocumentExtractor[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Create metadata with the resource name[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add conditional check for both `fetchHyperlinkContent` AND [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mshouldParseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only call `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if both conditions are met[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Move the `[0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call inside this conditional block[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m:** Modify `TextAndCSVParser.java` - [0m[1;35mprocessURL[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m273[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter creating metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, before line [0m[1;36m275[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore creating URL[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add URL scheme validation to reject non-[0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m protocols[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Log warning and return early if validation fails[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m:** Ensure existing functionality is preserved[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The HTML anchor tag generation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m258[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m260[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains unchanged[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Test case `[0m[1;35mtestHyperlink[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will continue to pass as it only validates anchor tag[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreation[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Hyperlinks are still extracted and displayed, just not fetched by default[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Users who need URL fetching can explicitly enable it via configuration[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why this is optimal:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows Tika patterns:** Mirrors PDFParserConfig's approach to [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity-sensitive features [0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractInlineImages[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Defense in depth:** Multiple layers prevent SSRF even if one layer is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmisconfigured[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Backwards compatible for display:** Hyperlinks are still converted to HTML [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39manchors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtest case passes[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Opt-in security:** Defaults to safe behavior, requires explicit enabling for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrisky features[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Respects existing controls:** Honors DocumentSelector, EmptyParser, and other [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity patterns[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Minimal code changes:** Focused changes to vulnerable methods only[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it preserves existing logic:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **HYPERLINK detection unchanged:** Pattern matching and anchor tag generation [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain identical[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Test compatibility:** The `[0m[1;35mtestHyperlink[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` test only validates anchor tag [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreation, which still works[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Configuration extensibility:** Uses existing `@Field` annotation pattern for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mXML configuration[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Embedded document flow:** When enabled, follows standard [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEmbeddedDocumentExtractor pattern[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Error handling preserved:** Exception catching and metadata recording remain [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it addresses the vulnerability:**[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Eliminates automatic URL fetching:** Network requests only happen when [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicitly configured[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Enforces security checks:** Validates both configuration AND [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mshouldParseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before fetching[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Prevents protocol abuse:** URL scheme validation blocks [0m[4;94mfile://,[0m[39m jar:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m, etc.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Provides user control:** Administrators can disable feature entirely via [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Clear security documentation:** Javadoc warns about SSRF risks when enabling [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfeature[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential side effects and mitigation:**[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Side effect:** Existing users who rely on URL fetching will see behavior [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** This is intentional - the current behavior is a security [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability. Users who need this feature can explicitly enable it with [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[33mfetchHyperlinkContent[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Side effect:** URL fetching now requires two configurations [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mfetchHyperlinkContent + not EmptyParser[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** This is defense in depth. It ensures multiple security [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrols must be bypassed[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Side effect:** Non-[0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m URLs are now rejected[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** This prevents [0m[4;94mfile://[0m[39m and other dangerous protocols. [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be sufficient for legitimate use cases[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix follows the same pattern as:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **PDFParserConfig.extractInlineImages**: Security-sensitive feature defaults to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse with warnings[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **[0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.shouldParseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Check before processing [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedded content  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **EmptyParser pattern**: Respect user's choice to disable embedded document [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **DocumentSelector**: Honor security policies configured in ParseContext[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * If <code>true<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>, the parser will attempt to fetch and parse the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontent[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * from URLs found in HYPERLINK formulas. Even when enabled, only HTTP and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHTTPS[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <b>SECURITY WARNING:<[0m[35m/[0m[95mb[0m[39m> Setting this to <code>true<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m> can expose your[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * application to Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m attacks. Malicious CSV [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiles[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * could contain URLs that:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <ul>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <li>Access internal network resources [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[4;94mhttp://localhost/admin[0m[4;94m)[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mli[0m[39m>[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <li>Exfiltrate data to external servers<[0m[35m/[0m[95mli[0m[39m>[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <li>Scan internal ports and services<[0m[35m/[0m[95mli[0m[39m>[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <li>Exploit internal services via crafted requests<[0m[35m/[0m[95mli[0m[39m>[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mul[0m[39m>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <p/>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * Set to <code>true<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m> only with the greatest caution and only when:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <ul>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <li>You trust the source of all CSV files being processed<[0m[35m/[0m[95mli[0m[39m>[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * <li>You have implemented additional security controls [0m[1;39m([0m[39mURL allowlists, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnetwork isolation, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mli[0m[39m>[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.csv.TextAndCSVParser.processCell[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTextAndCSVParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:261[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.csv.TextAndCSVParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTextAndCSVParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:211[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TextAndCSVParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTextAndCSVParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:4[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m1[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 092377579d0e2656[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue identifies a Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApache Tika's `TextAndCSVParser` class. The fuzzer detected that the parser [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to connect to external URLs [0m[1;39m([0m[39mspecifically `jazzer.com:[0m[1;36m443[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing CSV files containing hyperlinks, which could allow attackers to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexfiltrate sensitive data or access internal services through malicious CSV files.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt introduces a new configuration option `fetchHyperlinkContent` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `TextAndCSVConfig` to control whether URLs found in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHYPERLINK formulas should be fetched. The patch also adds URL scheme validation to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly allow HTTP/HTTPS protocols. However, the patch failed to compile due to syntax[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors in the modified `TextAndCSVParser.java` file, specifically around line [0m[1;36m72[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere incomplete class declaration modifications were made.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe SSRF vulnerability manifests when the `TextAndCSVParser` processes CSV files [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontaining hyperlinks. The stack trace shows:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The parser identifies a URL in a cell through the `processCell` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m261[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. It calls `processURL` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m278[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to handle the hyperlink[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The `processURL` method attempts to establish a connection to the URL using [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.net.URLConnection`[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. This triggers the fuzzer's SSRF detection when attempting to connect to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`jazzer.com:[0m[1;36m443[0m[39m`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in the `processURL` method where any URL found in CSV [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhyperlinks is automatically fetched and parsed without validation or security [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrols. This behavior allows untrusted CSV files to trigger arbitrary network [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequests from the server processing the file.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The issue occurs during CSV parsing at `TextAndCSVParser.processCell` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m261[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `processURL` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m278[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m unconditionally attempts to fetch remote [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontent[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No configuration exists to disable this behavior[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No URL validation or allowlisting is performed before making network requests[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch makes modifications to two files:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. TextAndCSVConfig.java modifications:**[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a new boolean field `fetchHyperlinkContent` with default value `false`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Includes comprehensive JavaDoc documentation warning about SSRF risks[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Provides getter and setter methods for the configuration option[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The modifications to this file appear syntactically correct[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. TextAndCSVParser.java modifications:**[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds Logger import statements for logging security warnings[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Attempts to modify the class structure starting at line [0m[1;36m66[0m[39m, including:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A new class declaration line that appears incomplete[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Attempts to add a SUPPORTED_TYPES constant declaration[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- At line [0m[1;36m264[0m[39m, adds conditional logic to check [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtextAndCSVConfig.isFetchHyperlinkContent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before calling `processURL`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds additional validation through [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`EmbeddedDocumentExtractor.shouldParseEmbedded` check[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- At line [0m[1;36m287[0m[39m in `processURL` method, adds URL scheme validation using regex [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`^https?:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95m.[0m[39m*` to only allow HTTP/HTTPS protocols[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds logging for blocked non-[0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m URLs[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Sets error metadata when URLs are blocked[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Compilation Errors:**[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe compilation fails with [0m[1;36m53[0m[39m errors starting at line [0m[1;36m72[0m[39m of [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TextAndCSVParser.java`. The errors indicate:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m72[0m[39m: [0m[32m"illegal start of expression"[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m73[0m[39m: Multiple syntax errors including missing parentheses and semicolons[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch appears to have corrupted the class declaration by inserting an [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincomplete statement:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  private static final Set<MediaType> SUPPORTED_TYPES = [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mCollections.unmodifiableSet[0m[1;39m([0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This line is incomplete and appears immediately after the class declaration, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbreaking the class structure[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The JavaDoc comment that was partially retained [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m72[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m78[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is now in an [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid position[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Multiple errors cascade from this initial corruption, affecting the parser's [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mability to interpret subsequent code[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and address this vulnerability, the following areas of the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase should be examined:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **TextAndCSVParser.java complete structure**: Review the full class [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation to understand where the SUPPORTED_TYPES field should be properly [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclared and how the patch inadvertently corrupted the class structure.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **processURL method implementation**: Examine the complete implementation of the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`processURL` method to understand what operations are performed on fetched URLs and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether there are other security implications beyond SSRF.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **EmbeddedDocumentExtractor usage**: Investigate how [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.getEmbeddedDocumentExtractor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` works and whether it [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovides any existing security controls that could be leveraged.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **HYPERLINK formula parsing**: Understand how hyperlinks are identified in CSV [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcells [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `processCell` method logic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to determine if the detection itself could [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe exploited.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Configuration system**: Review how `TextAndCSVConfig` is instantiated and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassed to the parser to ensure the new configuration option would be properly [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccessible.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Existing URL handling patterns**: Search for other parsers in the Tika [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase that handle URLs to identify if this is a systemic issue and to find [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatterns for secure URL handling.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Test coverage**: Examine existing tests for `TextAndCSVParser` to understand [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhat URL handling scenarios are currently tested and what additional security test [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases would be needed.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. **Default behavior impact**: Assess what existing functionality would break if [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mURL fetching is disabled by default, to understand backward compatibility [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplications.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
